{
  "texts": [
    "AdaLoRA [3] introduces dynamic rank allocation using singular value decomposition (SVD) and Hessian-based importance scores.",
    "This approach redistributes rank capacity across layers during training, assigning more rank to critical layers and reducing capacity in less important ones.",
    "Although this improves performance, it comes at the cost of significant computational overhead, since full-matrix decompositions and Hessian approximations need to be periodically computed, resulting in slower training and greater hardware requirements.",
    "DoRA and LongLoRA.",
    "Other variants, such as DoRA (Dynamic LoRA) and LongLoRA, explore rank adjustments or long-sequence optimization strategies."
  ]
}